      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Vanishing Point</hl1>
        <hl2 class="online_headline">The Vanishing Point</hl2>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Playwright August Wilson's latest offering Gem of the Ocean has shortest run of his Broadway productions, only 87 performances; listing of performance totals of his other plays; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>When ''Gem of the Ocean'' closed last Sunday at the Walter Kerr Theater after 87 performances, it was the shortest run for any of August Wilson's original Broadway productions. Here is a list of those productions, with the final total of performances for each; Mr. Wilson's next play, ''Radio Golf,'' will have its premiere at the Yale Repertory Theater on April 22.</p>
        <p>285  ''Ma Rainey's Black Bottom,'' 1984</p>
        <p>536  ''Fences,'' 1987</p>
        <p>116  ''Joe Turner's Come and Gone,'' 1988</p>
        <p>336  ''The Piano Lesson,'' 1990</p>
        <p>167  ''Two Trains Running,'' 1992</p>
        <p>201  ''Seven Guitars,'' 1996</p>
        <p>96  ''King Hedley II,'' 2001</p>
        <p>87  ''Gem of the Ocean,'' 2004</p>
      </block>
